On November 25, 2019, President Trump signed the Preventing Animal Cruelty and Torture Act into law. The legislation restricts the creation and distribution of videos or images of animal torture. The President expressed his appreciation for the individuals and organizations that worked hard to make this bill a reality. He emphasized the importance of combatting animal cruelty and stated that it should have happened a long time ago. The President also highlighted the role animals play in the development and security of the country. Various participants, including Representative Vern Buchanan and Sheriff Carolyn "Bunny" Welsh, commended the President for his leadership on this issue. They expressed gratitude for the passing of the bill and the support it provides for law enforcement agencies to investigate and prosecute animal cruelty. The President signed the bill and thanked everyone for their efforts.